addBorrower(uint256,address).details: Only called by the pool owner

addLender(uint256,address).details: Only called by the pool owner

borrowerVerification(uint256,address).details: returns a boolean and byte32 uuid.

params._loanExpirationTime: Length of time in seconds before pending loan expire.
params._paymentDefaultDuration: Length of time in seconds before a loan is considered in default for non-payment.
params._poolFeePercent: The pool fee percentage in bps.
params._poolId: The Id of the existing pool.

params._loanExpirationTime: Length of time in seconds before pending loan expire.
params._paymentDefaultDuration: Length of time in seconds before a loan is considered in default for non-payment.
params._poolFeePercent: The pool fee percentage in bps.
params._requireBorrowerAttestation: Boolean that indicates if borrowers require attestation to join pool.
params._requireLenderAttestation: Boolean that indicates if lenders require attestation to join pool.

returns.poolId_: The market ID of the newly created pool.

lenderVerification(uint256,address).details: returns a boolean and byte32 uuid.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

removeBorrower(uint256,address).details: Only called by the pool owner

removeLender(uint256,address).details: Only called by the pool owner

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._newPercent: The new percent to be set.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

addBorrower(uint256,address).notice: Adds a borrower to the pool.

addLender(uint256,address).notice: Adds a lender to the pool.

borrowerVerification(uint256,address).notice: Checks if the address is a verified borrower.

changePoolSetting(uint256,uint32,uint32,.notice: Change the details of existing pool.

lenderVerification(uint256,address).notice: Checks if the address is a verified lender.

removeBorrower(uint256,address).notice: Removes a borrower from the pool.

removeLender(uint256,address).notice: Removes a lender from the pool.

setPaymentDefaultDuration(uint256,uint32.notice: Sets the pool payment default duration.

setloanExpirationTime(uint256,uint32).notice: Sets the desired loan expiration time.
